ie.\n\"It is my pinion,\" said Mr. Mene\nfee today, \"that the money will be\navailable in cash next week.\" The\ndraft for this first installment of Ok\nlahoma's fund was executed last week\nby Assistant Secretary of State Mey\ner and with a certified copy of the\nlaw attached it\" was forwarded to the\nUnited States treasurer.\n\"This office is positively snowed\nunder with applications for loans\nfrom this fund,\" said Mr. Marr of the\npublic land commission today.\nBy, Wireless Telegraphy\nSnowdrift, Dakota, Dec. 21 To the Children of Chicka\nsha: I am coming: to Chickasha just s fast as my sleigh\nand reindeer can carry me. I ran into a big drift of snow here\nlast night, which nearly upset my sleigh, but I got out all\nrifc'ht and I'll be in Chickasha tonight, sure.. My! But it's\ncold up here; my beard is covered with icicles now and I'll be\nbe glad to get down there where it is -warm. I'm going to\nleave my sleigh here and will come to Chickasha in my auto\nmobile. Now, you must go to bed erly tonight and go to sleep. Do\nnot peep out from under the cover; if you do, I won't leave\nyou anything. I have bushels of pretty things for little boys\nand girls who are good. I want you to promise me to be good\nall next year. Mind your papas and mammas and old Santa\nwill remember you. Goddbye,\nYour old friend, SANTA CLAUS.\nMany Entertainments for thz L lit!: On\nThis Evening Gifts and Gccd Ch:er\nfor Everybody\nj. 4. j. .j. .j. 4-. -i' 4\" I 4 J\"! -I -J- 4 -I- \"1 I- 5 5 5 4 \"I -5 l\nCORRECTION.\nA heading to the story entitled:\nMystery of a Trunk,\" in last Satur\nday's paper, contained the line,:\n\"Trunk Goes Astray Between th: De\npot, and Hotel.\" This line stated a\nconclusion which could not be drawn\nfrom the article in wnmh the story\nof the affair as it occured was related.\n\"Merry, merry Christmas, every\nwhere,\" is the prevailing spirit of the\nweek, and the various Christmas en\ntertainments have already commenced.\nThe first was the beautiful canta\nta given by the members of the Christ\nian church last night in the opera\nhouse, and this was heartily applaud\ned by an appreciative audience. Many\nof the other churches will give Christ-\nf he transfer people say the trunk was 1 tv;\n1 1 1 mas entertainments and trees this ev-\ndelivered at the hotel and tnat they eningj and iarg0. crowds wiu be in at-\nhave ample testimony to prove it, tendance at all these festivities. There\nwhile Mr. Martin, the owner of the 'will be a pretty cantata at the Pres-\ntrunk, says it wis not, The latter byterlan church tonight in connection\ngatherings, as well as the usual round\nof holiday amusements and fun are\nalso looked forward to by everyone.\nAnticipation of the many celebrations\nof the birth anniversary of the\nChrist child 'has wrought Christmas\nenthusiasm up to its highest pitch\nand given all the true spirit of Christ\nmas peacefuiness and 'happiness.\nstated last night that .e 'had 'filed a\nsuit against both tue transfer com\npany and he proprietor of the fiotel\nfor the value of the property lost.\nIMTEBS' GUM!\nIN CONVENTION HALL, DECEMBER 27\nD L1ASQULRADE\nI\nwith a Christmas tree and a very\npopular Santa Claus, and the Metho\ndists will also give a very interest\ning entertainment for which much\ntime has been spent in the prepara\ntion. At 7:30 this evening a Christ\nmas tree at the Congregational church\nwill be the attraction for a great num-\nFAKE WITH TKE UEIAT\nWith \"The Cow Puncher,\" which\nwill be seen at the opera house on the\nevening of Dec. 30 will come Bee Gray\na Chickasha boy who has won fame\nas the champion trick lariat and rope\nspinner of the country. He will give\nan exhibition on horseback on the\nher of anxious children and not a few 1 street at two o'clock in the afternoon\nolder ones, and a short program will and will also do a trick lariat spe-\nOKLA. CBiTilAL\nDELAYED\nTHAT\nChristmas\nKodak\nLet u Lu )tu ttuw io use it.\nHow ea.-y it U U make home por\ntraits anil flash l